<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.248/11–1747</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chinese Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of
                            the Division of Chinese Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ringwalt</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-11-17">November 17,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Ringwalt</hi>: As you are aware, an agreement
                        has been signed in China regarding certain items of equipment and material
                        under the 8⅓ Group Program for the Chinese Air Force by representatives of
                        our two governments. I am directed by the Ambassador to express to you that
                        my government would appreciate it very much if instructions could be sent to
                        the United States representatives in China and the Pacific Zone to expedite
                        delivery of such items and material.</p>
                    <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shao-Hwa Tan</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>